<L>__{interior broadway theater backstage empty stage dusk}
<A>__{the curtains are still closed, and the sound of the audience excitedly murmuring behind them is heard. . stagehands are moving stage lights as }
<B>__{a stage manager}
<A>__{takes a nervous peek through the curtains to check the audience it's a full house. he holds a prop umbrella in one hand, anxiously checks his watch in the other. he looks on both wings of the stage and then relief floods his face as he sees the man in the grey suit hurrying over to him. the stage manager wordlessly hands him the umbrella and signals to a stagehand in the background. the curtains start to open and the murmur of the audience dies down.}
